Eradication or control of virus diseases is difficult given the complex and dynamic nature of virus epidemics and the great evolvability of viruses (
 Acosta-Leal et al., 2011; 
 Elena et al., 2014). For efficient and durable control, it is necessary to consider the genetic diversity and evolution of virus populations and have specific, fast and reliable diagnostic tools. Disease management in agriculture is based on two approaches: immunization to get resistant plants to viral infections and prophylactic measures to restrain virus dispersion.
